ToDoList Application

Overview
This ToDoList application is a JavaFX-based task management system that allows users to create, manage, and organize their tasks efficiently.

Features
- Add new tasks with title, description, due date, priority, and category
- Remove existing tasks
- Filter tasks by category
- Sort tasks by priority or due date
- Update task progress
- Support for different task types (generic tasks, meeting tasks, and project tasks)

Prerequisites
- Java Development Kit (JDK) 8 or higher
- JavaFX SDK (included in JDK 8, but needs to be added separately for JDK 11+)
- An IDE that supports Java and JavaFX 

Project Structure
com.javagiants.todolist/
├── controllers/
│   └── TaskController.java
├── models/
│   ├── Task.java
│   ├── MeetingTask.java
│   ├── ProjectTask.java
│   ├── TaskList.java
│   └── TaskType.java
├── views/
│   └── TaskView.fxml
└── Main.java

Setup Instructions
1. Clone the repository or download the source code.
2. Open the project in your preferred IDE.
3. Ensure that JavaFX is properly set up in your development environment.
4. Build the project to resolve any dependencies.

Running the Application
1. Locate the Main.java file in the project structure.
2. Run the main method in the Main class.
3. The application window should appear, displaying the ToDoList interface.

Using the Application
1. Adding a Task:
   - Fill in the task details in the provided fields.
   - Click the "Add Task" button to create a new task.

2. Removing a Task:
   - Select a task from the list.
   - Click the "Remove Task" button to delete the selected task.

3. Filtering Tasks:
   - Select a category from the dropdown.
   - Click the "Filter by Category" button to show tasks in that category.

4. Sorting Tasks:
   - Click "Sort by Priority" or "Sort by Due Date" to reorder the task list.

5. Updating Task Progress:
   - Select a task from the list.
   - Adjust the progress slider.
   - Click "Update Progress" to save the changes.

Customization
- To add new task types, extend the Task class and update the TaskController to handle the new type.
- Modify the TaskView.fxml file to change the layout or add new UI elements.

Troubleshooting
- If the application fails to start, ensure that JavaFX is properly configured in your project settings.
- For any NullPointerExceptions, check that all FXML elements are correctly linked to the controller.

